name: diphosphate---fructose-6-phosphate 1-phosphotransferase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: The enzyme catalyses a similar reaction to EC 2.7.1.11, 6-phosphofructokinase, but utilizes diphosphate instead of ATP as the the phosphate donor. It has been described in higher plants, primitive eukaryotes, bacteria, and archaea.
